data.enText: special importance that is given to sth

data.chText: 重点已经从制造业向服务行业转移。
data.enText: There has been a shift of emphasis from manufacturing to service industries.

data.chText: 重点主要放在学习口语上。
data.enText: The emphasis is very much on learning the spoken language.

data.chText: 这门课程着重职业培训。
data.enText: The course has a vocational emphasis.

data.chText: 我们提供各种信息服务，尤其是法律咨询。
data.enText: We provide all types of information, with an emphasis on legal advice.

data.chText: 我们将要观察的例子所强调的重点很不相同。
data.enText: The examples we will look at have quite different emphases.

data.chText: （对某个词或短语的）强调，加重语气，重读
data.enText: the extra force given to a word or phrase when spoken, especially in order to show that it is important; a way of writing a word (for example drawing a line underneath it) to show that it is important

data.chText: “我可以向你保证，”她加重语气补充道，“这些数字是正确的。”
data.enText: ‘I can assure you,’ she added with emphasis, ‘the figures are correct.’

means: (对某个词或短语的)强调，加重语气，重读

ex.chText: 道德问题是他讲话的重点。
ex.enText: Morality was the emphasis of his speech.

ex.chText: 这本书特别强调了空气污染问题。
ex.enText: This book places a special emphasis on air pollution.

synonyms.bx: 指尽力突出的重点或重要性。

ex.chText: 他发表了讲话，重点在教育方面。
ex.enText: He gave a speech with the accent on education.

ex.chText: 该公司把重点放在新信息技术上面。
ex.enText: The company put the accent on new information technology.

ex.chText: 他强调诚实是一种重要的美德。
ex.enText: He lays stress/emphasis on honesty as an important virtue.

ex.chText: 我们现在的工作重点应该放在农业上。
ex.enText: The stress/emphasis of our work should now be on agriculture.

synonyms.bx: 可与 emphasis 换用，侧重指对某一观念、事实、活动等给予的特别关注或重视。

tr: the relative prominence of a syllable or musical note (especially with regard to stress or pitch)
example: he put the stress on the wrong syllable

tr: special and significant stress by means of position or repetition e.g.

example: the red light gave the central figure increased emphasis
the room was decorated in shades of grey with distinctive red accents

value.def: Emphasis is special or extra importance that is given to an activity or to a part or aspect of something.

example.ex: Too much emphasis is placed on research...
example.tran: 过分强调研究的重要性。

example.ex: Grant puts a special emphasis on weather in his paintings.
example.tran: 格兰特在他的绘画中特别注重天气。

value.def: Emphasis is extra force that you put on a syllable, word, or phrase when you are speaking in order to make it seem more important.

example.ex: 'I might have known it!' Miss Burnett said with emphasis...
example.tran: “我早该料到了！”伯内特小姐加重语气说。

example.ex: The emphasis is on the first syllable of the last word.
example.tran: 重音在最后一个单词的第一个音节上。

value.tran: （对音节、单词或短语的）强调，重读

trans: 重视；强调；注重；把重点放在；着重于
